OpenBlox

This directory tree contains libopenblox, the core of the OpenBlox
game engine.

The file INSTALL in this directory tells you how to build and install
this daemon on various systems.

The file HACKING contains information on contributing to this project
as a developer.

You may encounter bugs in this software. If you do, please report them.
Bug reports are very valuable to the OpenBlox project, since they allow
us to notice and fix problems we don't have on our machines, or in code
we don't use often. Please report them using the issue tracker provided
at <https://git.openblox.org/openblox/libopenblox/issues>.

If nobody notices quickly, you may also find it useful to discuss the
issue on one of the OpenBlox mailing lists, best suited to your
issue. You can find a list of all OpenBlox mailing lists at
https://lists.openblox.org/cgi-bin/mailman/listinfo

You may also get in contact using the Internet Relay Chat protocol.
OpenBlox developers can usually be found in the channel #OpenBlox on
the Freenode IRC network.

